						<div class="postbody">It's pretty hard to even being to grasp what exactly you mean by some of these ideas.  They are pretty vague on how exactly you imagine to implement them since how many of the parts are imaginary at this point...  So there isn't much ability to begin to analyze what will work and what won't.  In general I'd say most of the things you're trying to do are with an underpowered piece of hardware, but I really don't know what half of these ideas are.<br /> <br />Q: Could you possibly somehow, connect two things and have a random PPU register to maybe control something?<br />A: Sure, connect an FPGA to every pin on the NES/FC mobo and you can do anything...</div>

					
